    {
      "id": "1140913502430126",
      "score": 1,
      "review_title": "Awful.",
      "review_description": "The movement is asinine. As bouncy as Ug and as heavy as Gtag, I feel like a beach ball... again. And no turning? Not even snap turning? Epic fail. And parkour is nonexistant- you'll either try and use a Gorilla Tag movement option- pinchclimb, walljump, cornerclimb- and not be able to do it, or skid right out of control when simply platforming.\n\nThe objective of the game is nonexistant. Or perhaps it was explained to me while I was ragdolled and couldn't actually see anything but the floor. Is it an extraction? An exploration game? Or is it just another walking sim.\n\nThe 3D models are alright, and the player models look nicely silly- but to my dismay and disgust, AI-generated imagery is used for seemingly every 2D asset, from the cosmetic backgrounds to the signs of the Infinite Ikea map. I am worried that the 3D models may be generated as well.\n\nThe Death system is viciously stupid. From a bear trap on the ground to a big hole to a monster walking within 10 feet of you, you will die without fanfare or even a sound effect, then appear back at spawn, ready to enjoy the nothingburger all over again.\n\nI can only hope that this game is in Beta and will improve, because right now, the best part is seeing other players have fun.\nAt least someone is able to enjoy this Unity program.",
      "date": 1777131953,
      "review_helpful_count": 66,
      "author_display_name": "Greenostrich270",
      "author_alias": "Greenostrich270",
      "developer_response": null
    },
